# Parallel Test Runner Configuration for Node.js Target
#
# Compiles the parallel test runner to JavaScript for execution with Node.js
# This provides better process management than the eval target
#
# Usage:
#   haxe test/ParallelTestJS.hxml && node test/parallel-runner.js
#   haxe test/ParallelTestJS.hxml && node test/parallel-runner.js test=arrays
#   haxe test/ParallelTestJS.hxml && node test/parallel-runner.js update-intended
#
# Benefits over eval target:
# - Non-blocking process management
# - Proper async/await support
# - No file locking issues
# - Better error handling

# Main class
-main test.ParallelTestRunnerNode

# Class paths
-cp test

# Required libraries
-lib hxnodejs

# Target: JavaScript for Node.js
-js test/parallel-runner.js

# Use modern JavaScript features
-D js-es=6

# Mark as Node.js target
-D nodejs

# Optional: Enable source maps for debugging
# -D js-source-map